dcterms:description: A dataset of handwritten digits used for training image processing systems. The MNIST dataset consists of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images, each representing a single digit from 0 to 9.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. The CIFAR10 dataset is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR10

dcterms:description: A derived dataset created for the purpose of binary optimization in the context of the research presented in this paper. It consists of inputs predicted as a specific class and an equal number of randomly selected inputs not predicted as that class.
dcterms:title: Dc_o
